The paper deals with image retagging, which is a task related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves constructing a graph and using tensor completion, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and data mining (cs.SI). Finally, the paper evaluates the method on a real-world social image database, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM).
